    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Puzzles composed of several parts that pose a problem for one person to solve by manipulation using logic, reasoning, insight, luck, or dexterity.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000033941/Slocum and Botermans, Puzzles (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Rompecabezas compuestos de varias partes que proponen un problema para ser resuelto por una persona por manipulación usando lógica, razonamiento, perspicacia, suerte, o destreza.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Puzzels die bestaan uit verschillende stukken en die een vraagstuk vormen dat door één persoon kan worden opgelost door de stukken te manipuleren met behulp van logica, redenatie, inzicht, geluk of behendigheid.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
